cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.CE, cs.SE, cs.ET

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper focuses on optimizing electricity cost in data centers, which is a key concern in distributed and cluster computing. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes an optimization framework that captures the cost of electricity and the benefit from regulation markets, which falls under the domain of systems and control. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper uses real data from Microsoft data center traces and PJM regulation signals to demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed optimization framework, which involves computational engineering and finance. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper may involve software engineering aspects related to implementing the proposed optimization framework in data centers. 
- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies): The paper discusses the emerging trend of using energy storage devices to actively shape power consumption in data centers, which falls under the domain of emerging technologies.
